Shout out to all the Changemakers! I'm proud to announce @vjessesmithformayor, co-founder of the Community Action League, and native of my hometown Palmdale as my nominee for #ChimeInForChangeMakers! Jessie's dedication, tremendous leadership, and passion for social justice embody what the #ChimeInForChangemakers campaign is all about. Now it's your turn! Chime in if you know someone doing something to make a positive impact within their community and give them a chance to win $10,000 towards their cause and $2,000 for yourself! 

Here’s how to enter: 

Follow @chime on Instagram
-Create a new post nominating someone making a difference in your community. Tell @chime what they’re doing and why they should be recognized.
-Include the hashtags #ChimeInForChangemakers and #Contest in the caption and tag @chime in the post. If your nominee has an Instagram account, please tag them!

Deadline for entries is 11:59pm ET on September 27, 2020. 25 nominations will be selected. Subject to Official Rules. Visit chime.com/changemakers-rules for details. Private accounts must be public for submission to be seen. Potential winners will be subject to a background check to claim the award.

node.text: 🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾 Mike @artmobb you killed this piece thank you bro! One of my fav moments with my idol was the 2016 all star game in Toronto. It was a special night for many reasons and the biggest being Kobe’s final all star game. We met at the scorers table to be checked back into the game. I had been feeling good the start of the game and told Kobe I’m going for the scoring record and the all star game MVP. He told me that’s how it goes you get hot early it’s over. We laughed about it as he told me to keep going don’t let up. I finished with 41 which I believe tied the record at that point and the west team was triple teaming me to not score again 🖕🏾 lol. But this moment was special to me and thank you Mike for bringing it back to life! Hope you can see the brighter days for us in heaven Kobe. We love and miss you and will always! Great touch with @louwillville on the sounds!
